<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="45" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
<taxonomicName class="Pezizomycetes" family="Helvellaceae" genus="Helvella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Helvella acetabuloides" order="Pezizales" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="acetabuloides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Helvella acetabuloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is nested with 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. acetabulum" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="acetabulum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">H. acetabulum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. arctoalpina" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="arctoalpina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">H. arctoalpina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. costata" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="costata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">H. costata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. sichuanensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="sichuanensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">H. sichuanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Clade 3 (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Bayesian phylogenetic tree of Helvella and Dissingia inferred from combined Hsp 90, ITS 2, LSU and TEF 1 dataset. Posterior probability values ≥ 0.90 (left) and bootstrap values ≥ 70 % (right) are indicated at nodes." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.60.38186.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/352437" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" tableDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.60.38186.figure1">Figure 1</figureCitation>
). Its hymenium is reddish-brown when dry and different from that of 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. acetabulum" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="acetabulum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">H. acetabulum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(brown when dry) and those of 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. arctoalpina" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="arctoalpina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">H. arctoalpina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. sichuanensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="sichuanensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">H. sichuanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(black when dry, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.29203/ka.1977.124" author="Harmaja, H" journalOrPublisher="Karstenia" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" pagination="45 - 48" refId="B16" refString="Harmaja, H, 1977b. A revision of the Helvellaacetabulum group (Pezizales) in Fennoscandia. Karstenia 17: 45 - 48" title="A revision of the Helvellaacetabulum group (Pezizales) in Fennoscandia." url="https://doi.org/10.29203/ka.1977.124" volume="17" year="1977 b">Harmaja 1977b</bibRefCitation>
). The two specimens cited are identical in sequences of 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Hsp90</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName class="Pezizomycetes" family="Helvellaceae" genus="Helvella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Helvella acetabuloides" order="Pezizales" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="acetabuloides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Helvella acetabuloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. acetabulum" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="acetabulum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">H. acetabulum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 6 bp for Hsp90 (H410, epitype), 14 bp for ITS2 (HMAS 243823) and 17 bp for TEF1 (H133). It is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. arctoalpina" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="arctoalpina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">H. arctoalpina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 2 bp of Hsp90 (H293, holotype) and 11 bp of TEF1 (H033), from 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. costata" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="costata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">H. costata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 3 bp of Hsp90. It differs from 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. sichuanensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="sichuanensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">H. sichuanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 1 bp of Hsp90, 20 bp of ITS2 and 11 bp of TEF1. PCR amplification of LSU failed.
</paragraph>
